+### 2.1 â€” `asw.smali`: ImageReader acquireLatestImage Patch
+
+**File:** `smali/asw.smali` Â· **Class:** `Lasw;` Â· **Dex:** `classes.dex`
+
+**Change:**
+```diff
+-    invoke-virtual {p1}, Landroid/media/ImageReader;->acquireNextImage()Landroid/media/Image;
++    invoke-virtual {p1}, Landroid/media/ImageReader;->acquireLatestImage()Landroid/media/Image;
+      move-result-object p1
++     if-eqz p1, :cond_0
+```
+
+| Aspect | Detail |
+|---|---|
+| **Original** | `acquireNextImage()` â€” returns oldest pending image. Queue grows unbounded if consumer is slower than producer â†’ memory pressure â†’ GC thrash. |
+| **Replacement** | `acquireLatestImage()` â€” returns most recent image, drops older pending frames. Standard recommendation for real-time preview. |
+| **Null guard** | `acquireLatestImage()` can return `null` (unlike `acquireNextImage()`). `if-eqz` jumps to cleanup if no frame available. |
+| **Impact** | Reduces memory pressure, eliminates queued-frame backlog, smooths preview. |
+| **KernelSU note** | Trivial replacement + 2 line null guard. No dependencies. |
