+### 2.7 â€” `sgcam/Shamim.smali`: Feature Patches + Preview Lag Fix
+
+**File:** `smali_classes3/sgcam/Shamim.smali` Â· **Class:** `Lsgcam/Shamim;` Â· **Dex:** `classes3.dex`
+
+**Role:** Central utility/helper class for all SGCAM-specific features.
+
+#### Patch A â€” Removed AWB Debug Logging (line ~495)
+
+```diff
+-    const-string v1, "COLOR_CORRECTION_GAINS original from system"
+-    invoke-static {v1, v5}, Lsgcam/logcat/LogcatGenerator;->GetAllArrayTypeValue(Ljava/lang/String;Ljava/lang/Object;)V
+-    const-string v1, "COLOR_CORRECTION_GAINS fills with 1.0f"
+-    invoke-static {v1, v6}, Lsgcam/logcat/LogcatGenerator;->GetAllArrayTypeValue(Ljava/lang/String;Ljava/lang/Object;)V
+```
+
+Removed 2 logcat array dumps inside an `Arrays.equals(gains, fillArray)` block. Cleanup of dev debug logging.
+
+#### Patch B â€” `GetAwbGain()`: Exynos AWB Override (line 1771)
+
+**Full new method:**
+```smali
+.method public static GetAwbGain(Ljcq;Lcom/google/googlex/gcam/FloatArray4;)Lcom/google/googlex/gcam/FloatArray4;
+    .locals 10
+    invoke-static {}, Lsgcam/default/DeviceCodeNames;->IdentifyExynos()Z
+    move-result v0
+    if-eqz v0, :cond_non_exynos_awb
+    const/4 v0, 0x4
+    new-array v0, v0, [F
+    fill-array-data v0, :array_exynos_awb
+    invoke-static {v0, p1}, Lsgcam/Shamim;->ConvertFArrayToFArray4(...)
+    move-result-object v0
+    return-object v0
+    :cond_non_exynos_awb
+    # ... original SENSOR_NEUTRAL_COLOR_POINT logic ...
+    :array_exynos_awb
+    .array-data 4
+        0x3f800000    # 1.0f
+        0x3f800000    # 1.0f
+        0x3f800000    # 1.0f
+        0x3f800000    # 1.0f
+    .end array-data
+.end method
+```
+
+| Aspect | Detail |
+|---|---|
+| **Why** | Google's AWB using `SENSOR_NEUTRAL_COLOR_POINT` produces wrong colors on Exynos ISPs. Unity gains `[1.0,1.0,1.0,1.0]` let the HAL handle AWB internally. |
+| **Dependencies** | `IdentifyExynos()`, `ConvertFArrayToFArray4()` |
+
+#### Patch C â€” `GetBlackLevel()`: Exynos Black Level Override (line 2165)
+
+**Full new method â€” On Exynos, reads 4 user-configurable black levels:**
+```
+levels[0] = ConvertStringToFloat(SetLensValue("pref_manual_black_level_1_key"), "193.5")
+levels[1] = ConvertStringToFloat(SetLensValue("pref_manual_black_level_2_key"), "193.5")
+levels[2] = ConvertStringToFloat(SetLensValue("pref_manual_black_level_3_key"), "193.5")
+levels[3] = ConvertStringToFloat(SetLensValue("pref_manual_black_level_4_key"), "193.5")
+```
+
+| Aspect | Detail |
+|---|---|
+| **Channel order** | `[R, G, G, B]` (Bayer RGGB) |
+| **Default 193.5** | Expected black level for Sony IMX616 on Exynos 9611 (A51). Qualcomm default is typically 64.0/128.0. |
+| **User-configurable** | Values from SharedPreferences via `LensValue.SetLensValue()` + `SharedPrefValues.ConvertStringToFloat()`. |
+| **Non-Exynos path** | Unchanged â€” reads `pref_black_level_key` int, packed-switch, or `SENSOR_BLACK_LEVEL_PATTERN`. |
+
+#### Patch D â€” `GetDefaultString()`: SharedPreferences Caching (line 4444)
+
+**New static field:**
+```smali
+.field private static sDefaultStringPrefs:Landroid/content/SharedPreferences;
+```
+
+Same lazy-init pattern as `Pref.smali`. Caches SharedPreferences in static field. Sister methods `GetDefaultStringSet()` and `GetDefaultDouble()` are NOT yet cached.
+
+#### Patch E â€” Preview Lag Fix v2 (`GetSliderPref`) (line 7186)
+
+**Hook point:** `GetSliderPref(Liyn;)Liyn;` â€” called by `ixn.k()` for every key set on the preview request builder. This is the **confirmed** hook (GetC2apiPref is NOT called for preview).
+
+**4 capture request overrides appended before `return-object p0`:**
+
+```smali
+# Debug marker
+const-string v5, "PREVIEW_LAG_FIX_V2"
+const-string v1, "GetSliderPref patch executing"
+invoke-static {v5, v1}, Landroid/util/Log;->e(Ljava/lang/String;Ljava/lang/String;)I
+
+# Patch 1: CONTROL_MODE = AUTO (1)
+sget-object v5, CaptureRequest.CONTROL_MODE
+const/4 v1, 0x1
+invoke-static {v1}, Integer;->valueOf(I)Ljava/lang/Integer;
+move-result-object v1
+invoke-virtual {p0, v5, v1}, Liyn;->b(Liyn;CaptureRequest$Key;Object;)V
+
+# Patch 2: STATISTICS_FACE_DETECT_MODE = OFF (0)
+sget-object v5, CaptureRequest.STATISTICS_FACE_DETECT_MODE
+const/4 v1, 0x0
+# ... same pattern ...
+
+# Patch 3: CONTROL_AE_TARGET_FPS_RANGE = [15, 30]
+sget-object v5, CaptureRequest.CONTROL_AE_TARGET_FPS_RANGE
+new-instance v6, Landroid/util/Range;
+const/16 v1, 0xf  # 15
+const/16 v2, 0x1e # 30
+invoke-direct {v6, v1, v2}, Landroid/util/Range;-><init>(Comparable;Comparable;)V
+invoke-virtual {p0, v5, v6}, Liyn;->b(Liyn;CaptureRequest$Key;Object;)V
+
+# Patch 4: STATISTICS_OIS_DATA_MODE = OFF (0)
+sget-object v5, CaptureRequest.STATISTICS_OIS_DATA_MODE
+const/4 v1, 0x0
+# ... same pattern ...
+```
+
+| # | Key | Value | HAL Default | Effect |
+|---|---|---|---|---|
+| 1 | `CONTROL_MODE` | `AUTO (1)` | `USE_SCENE_MODE=2` | Prevents scene-mode reprocessing pipeline |
+| 2 | `STATISTICS_FACE_DETECT_MODE` | `OFF (0)` | `FULL (128)` | Stops face-detect reprocessing every frame |
+| 3 | `CONTROL_AE_TARGET_FPS_RANGE` | `[15, 30]` | `[8, 30]` | Forces min 15 fps (HAL default lets it drop to 8) |
+| 4 | `STATISTICS_OIS_DATA_MODE` | `OFF (0)` | `ON (1)` | Prevents null OIS data errors |
+
+**Performance:** Before: 108â€“163ms/frame (6.67fps, 216 dropped frames/15s). After: ~33ms/frame (30fps).
+
+**Registers:** `v5` = key reusable, `v1` = value (except patch 3 uses `v2`, `v6`). `p0` = Liyn mutated in-place.
