+
+### 5.4 â€” Potential Issues
+
+| Issue | Details |
+|---|---|
+| **Smali â‰  DEX bytecode** | KernelSU patches operate on compiled DEX, not smali. Offsets vary between apktool versions. |
+| **Method size limits** | Methods exceeding 65536 bytes of bytecode after patching will be rejected by the DEX validator. |
+| **Register accounting** | Patches adding instructions (e.g., `dws.smali`) must verify register allocation doesn't conflict. |
+| **New method addition** | `Pref.getSharedPreferences()` adds a new method â€” requires adding entry to class method table in DEX. |
+| **New static fields** | `sDefaultStringPrefs` (Shamim), `appSharedPreferences` (Pref) â€” require field table entries. |
+| **String injection** | `"RawProcessing"` in `dws.smali` requires adding a string to the DEX string pool. |
